Let me square both sides to eliminate the square roots, but first, let's rearrange: sqrt(25 -b^2)*sqrt(9 +8b -b^2)= -b*(4 -b) Square both sides: (25 -b^2)(9 +8b -b^2)=b²(4 -b)² Expand left side: 25*(9 +8b -b^2) -b²*(9 +8b -b^2) =225 +200b -25b² -9b² -8b³ +b^4 =225 +200b -34b² -8b³ +b^4 Right side: b²*(16 -8b +b²)=16b² -8b³ +b^4 Set equal: 225 +200b -34b² -8b³ +b^4=16b² -8b³ +b^4 Subtract right side from left: 225 +200b -34b² -8b³ +b
